The PV converter can be considered as grid-supplier converter, which injects the reference active and reactive power. The reference output current is formed by the active and reactive power components ip and iq, respectively. This current is used in a hysteresis current band of 1 % width, in order to form the SPWM. The control scheme of the PV converter is presented in Fig. 4. The amplitude of the current iref is formed by the currents ip and iq, while the angle from the PLL angle θPLL and the reference angle φref as follows:10iref=ip2+iq2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
